  5, 'Once upon a time', 'Once upon a time, in a quaint village nestled between rolling hills, there lived a young girl named Elara. She was known for her adventurous spirit and insatiable curiosity. One day, while exploring the woods, Elara stumbled upon a hidden pathway she had never seen before. Driven by curiosity, she followed the path deeper into the forest until she came upon a clearing bathed in golden sunlight. In the center stood a magnificent tree with branches reaching towards the sky. Entranced, Elara approached the tree and noticed a small, intricately carved door at its base. With trembling hands, she pushed the door open and was greeted by a magical sight. Inside the tree was a cozy room adorned with twinkling fairy lights and shelves filled with ancient tomes.', '2024-04-20', 27);

